Grade 7 CBC Notes
Kenya Curriculum (CBC)
Fun, simple, and colorful learning notes for students

Mathematics

Topic 1: Decimals

Decimals are numbers with a point separating the whole number from the fractional part.
Examples:
0.5 = five tenths
2.75 = two wholes and seventy-five hundredths
Exercise:
Convert 3/4 to decimal
Add 1.25 + 2.7

Topic 2: Area of Shapes

Definition: Area = space covered by a shape
Examples:
Rectangle: L = 6cm, W = 4cm → Area = 6 × 4 = 24 cm²
Triangle: Base = 5cm, Height = 4cm → Area = ½ × 5 × 4 = 10 cm²
Exercise:
Find the area of a square with side 8cm

English

Topic 1: Verbs
Definition: Words that show actions
Examples: run, jump, eat, write
Exercise:
Underline the verbs in:
“The girl runs to school and eats lunch quickly.”

Topic 2: Tenses

Definition: Tense shows time of action (past, present, future)
Examples:
Past: I walked to school
Present: I walk to school
Future: I will walk to school
Exercise:
Change these sentences to past tense:
“He plays football.”
“They study math.”

Science

Topic 1: Human Digestive System

Food is broken down in the body so nutrients can be absorbed.
Main organs: Mouth, Esophagus, Stomach, Intestines
Exercise:
Name 3 organs in the digestive system

Topic 2: States of Matter (Advanced)

Matter can change states when heated or cooled.
Examples:
Water → Ice (freezing)
Water → Steam (boiling)
Exercise:
Give 2 examples of matter changing from gas to liquid

Social Studies

Topic 1: Kenyan Counties

Kenya has 47 counties. Each has a Governor.
Examples: Nairobi, Mombasa, Kisumu
Exercise:
Name 5 counties in Kenya

Topic 2: Government Roles

Leaders help run the country: President, Governors, Members of Parliament.
Exercise: Match the role with the responsibility:
President → _____
Governor → _____
